The paper deals with the organization of API-related knowledge, which is a common problem in software engineering (cs.SE). The use of machine learning techniques to classify different types of knowledge in API documentation suggests a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of statistical and semantic combinations, which are common techniques in information retrieval (cs.IR) and natural language processing (cs.CL). Finally, the paper's focus on taxonomy and classification suggests a connection to machine learning (cs.LG).
